  <static seed="222" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/QuadraticEquations/solveQuad365.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve the equation.</p>
<p><m>{x^{3}+11x^{2}+18x} = 0</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="20" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left\{0,-2,-9\right\}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>There are a few ways to solve quadratic equations- the easiest way to solve this particular 
type of problem is to use the <em>zero product principle</em>.</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
                {x^{3}+11x^{2}+18x} = 0 \amp \Rightarrow {x\mathopen{}\left(x+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+9\right)}=0\\
                                \amp \Rightarrow x=0\text{ or }x=-2\text{ or } x=-9\\
        \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Each solution can be checked by substituting it into the original equation- this is left as an exercise.</p>
</solution>
